## Required page structure

Every page must begin with YAML frontmatter:

```yaml
---
title: "Klarer, beschreibender Titel"
description: "Prägnante Beschreibung des Seiteninhalts"
---
```

- Titles for lore pages use the English proper noun (e.g. "The Breach", "Frontier Prime")
- Titles for guide pages use German (e.g. "Währungen", "Boons & Blights")
- Descriptions are always in German

## Content quality standards

- Use realistic, lore-consistent examples — reference actual factions, dimensions, and mechanics
- Cross-link related content: guide pages link to lore, lore pages link to guides
- Maintain consistent terminology from the glossary above
- Use descriptive alt text for all images
- Ensure proper heading hierarchy (H1 for page title, H2 for sections, H3 for subsections)
- Structure content for scannability: clear headings, tables, lists, and white space

## Component selection logic

- Use **Steps** for procedures and sequential instructions in guides
- Use **Tabs** for rift types, faction comparisons, or dimension-specific variants
- Use **Accordions** for theories, deep-dive lore, or optional detail
- Use **Cards/CardGroup** for cross-linking related entries (end of every lore page)
- Use **Tables** for structured comparisons (faction relationships, rift properties, reputation levels)
- Use **Note/Tip/Warning** contextually based on content type (see callout guidelines above)
